{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770317348,"nonce":"YpBF0QZEIHdT4prZ4SN0TXXxQaY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oo2bj","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/168","origin":"github"},"title":"Fix broken layers symlink in git","message":"## Problem\n\nThe `layers/` directory was accidentally committed as a broken symlink pointing to `../../layers` (which doesn't exist) in commit 2df7ca1.\n\n## Impact\n\n- Main workspace cannot access actual workspace layers\n- `layers` shows as broken symlink: `layers -\u003e ../../layers`\n- Blocks workspace initialization and ROS builds\n\n## Root Cause\n\nSymlink was accidentally created and committed, likely during worktree operations.\n\n## Solution\n\n1. Remove broken symlink from git tracking\n2. Ensure `layers/` remains in .gitignore\n3. Recreate layers/ directory structure using setup scripts\n4. Verify workspace can be initialized properly\n\n## Notes\n\n- `layers/` is already in .gitignore and should never be tracked\n- Contains ROS workspace build artifacts managed by vcstool/colcon\n- Work within layers has been committed to respective repos","files":null}]}